Recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to: 

a)	start the process and implement appropriate steps that would lead to the closure of the open dump and would result to switching to sanitary landfill;

b)	intensify efforts to achieve and embrace the full concept of Ecological solid waste management and adhere to the provisions of R.A. 9003 and their 10 Year Solid Waste Management Plan; 

c)	discontinue the practice of collecting non-segregated waste and come up with measures that would help its cause.  Encouraging waste segregation at source will also be beneficial in transitioning from an open dumpsite to a sanitary land fill as it would lessen the amount of wastes that would go to this dumpsite; and

d)	adopt scheduling method/scheme which would allow the collection of different types of wastes on different days. Data on waste characterization can aid in coming up with an effective scheduling scheme.

